  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hydrogeological Study Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the northern parts of Burkina Faso, where security issues keep on increasing and hundreds of thousands of people have fled their homes, water is becoming more and more scarce. The main problem is the lack of drinking water, but also for economic activities water is essential.Whereas the main focus of humanitarian interventions in these regions is on social issues, economic development is essential as well, especially when it comes to giving youth living in these areas perspective on a bright future.This project will map the current hydrogeological status of 8 cities in Burkina Faso and present recommendations on how to make water available; now and in the future. These outcomes will help NGOs and the Burkinabe Government in deciding which kinds of projects related to water, private sector development and/or entrepreneurship can be developed in these specific areas, and if needed adapt their policies in certain regions.</narrative>
  </description>
